    • Method Detail

      • getDataFolder

        File getDataFolder()
        Returns the folder that the plugin data's files are located in. The folder may not yet exist.

        See org.bukkit.plugin.Plugin#getDataFolder() within Bukkit
        See net.md_5.bungee.api.plugin.Plugin#getDataFolder() within BungeeCord API

        Returns:
        the data folder of this plugin

      • getLogger

        Logger getLogger()
        Returns the plugin logger associated with this server's logger. The returned logger automatically tags all log messages with the plugin's name.

        See org.bukkit.plugin.Plugin#getLogger() within Bukkit
        See net.md_5.bungee.api.plugin.Plugin#getLogger() within BungeeCord API

        Returns:
        Logger associated with this plugin

      • getResource

        InputStream getResource(String path)
        Gets an embedded resource in this plugin, within the jar or container. Care must be taken to close the returned stream.

        See org.bukkit.plugin.Plugin#getResource(String) within Bukkit
        See net.md_5.bungee.api.plugin.Plugin#getResourceAsStream(String) within BungeeCord API

        Parameters:
        path - the full path name of this resource
        Returns:
        the stream for getting this resource, or null if it does not exist

      • getType

        IBasicPlugin.Type getType()
        Returns the type of plugin this is.
        Returns:
        the type of plugin this is
